# What is Microsoft? 
Microsoft is a multinational technology company that is one of the most largest and influential software companies in the world. 
# What Microsoft does?
  1. Software
    a. Windows (PC operating system) b. Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, PowerPoint)
  2. Cloud Computing
    a. Microsoft Azure- used for business to run apps, store data, and more
  3. Hardware
    a. Computer Hardware  (PC Ecosystem) Surface Device Family
      a.Laptops & Hybrids b. Desktop Systems c. Accessories
    b. gaming hardware (XBOX Ecosystem)
      a. Consoles b. Controllers & Accessories c. Cloud/Hybring Gaming Hardware Angle
    c. mobile hardware (Direct & Indirect)
      a. Smartphones orginially Nokia but phased out Microsoft exited the smartphone OS market
      b. Dual-Screen/Android Devices c. Mobile Ecosystem Hardware Strategy (Microsoft now focuses on Apps/Services on Android and iOS
    d. Specialized/Emerging Hardware 
      a. Mixed Reality (AR/VR) - Microsoft HoloLens b. AI & Cloud Hardware (Indirect) - Microsoft designs custom hardware for Azure data centers
    *Takeaway- Microsoft's hardware strategy is ecosystem-drive, not volume-driven; Surface - productivity & Computing, XBOX- gaming ecosystem, Cloud + AI - backend infrastructure
  4. Services & Platform
      a. Microsoft Teams b. LinkedIn
